6 Multigeneration analysis

Model: \[ y = X\gamma + Z_g u_g + Z_b u_b + e \]

For the blocks effect in generations where the experiments were installed in incomplete blocks, the variance-covariance structure for diagonal heterogeneous Gb (DIAG) was used in all models. \[ G_b = \text{DIAG} = \begin{bmatrix} \sigma_1^2 & 0 & 0 \\ 0 & \sigma_2^2 & 0 \\ 0 & 0 & \sigma_3^2 \end{bmatrix} \]

6.1 Identity covariance structure (IDV) for G, variance components for R and Diagonal for B

\[ G_g = \text{IDV} = \begin{bmatrix} \sigma_1^2 & 0 & 0 & 0 \\ 0 & \sigma_1^2 & 0 & 0 \\ 0 & 0 & \sigma_1^2 & 0 \\ 0 & 0 & 0 & \sigma_1^2 \end{bmatrix} \] \[ R = VC = \begin{bmatrix} \sigma^2 & 0 & 0 & 0 \\ 0 & \sigma^2 & 0 & 0 \\ 0 & 0 & \sigma^2 & 0 \\ 0 & 0 & 0 & \sigma^2 \end{bmatrix} \]

> M1 = asreml(fixed =  Yield  ~ Generation + Rep:Generation + Pop:at(Generation, "F4:6"),
+             random = ~ Genotype:idv(Generation) + Block:at(Generation, c("F4:7", "F4:8", "F4:9")),
+             residual = ~ units,
+             na.action = na.method(x = "include", y = "include"),
+             data = data)

6.2 Identity covariance structure (IDV) for G, Diagonal for B and R

\[ G_g = \text{IDV} = \begin{bmatrix} \sigma_1^2 & 0 & 0 & 0 \\ 0 & \sigma_1^2 & 0 & 0 \\ 0 & 0 & \sigma_1^2 & 0 \\ 0 & 0 & 0 & \sigma_1^2 \end{bmatrix} \]

From here to the last model, the variance-covariance structure adopted for R was the heterogeneous diagonal structure (DIAG)

\[ R = \text{DIAG} = \begin{bmatrix} \sigma_{11}^2 & 0 & 0 & 0 \\ 0 & \sigma_{22}^2 & 0 & 0 \\ 0 & 0 & \sigma_{33}^2 & 0 \\ 0 & 0 & 0 & \sigma_{44}^2 \end{bmatrix} \]

> psi = diag(sum.m8[grep("var", rownames(sum.m8)),1])
> lamblamb.star = mat.loadings.star %*% t(mat.loadings.star)
> expvar8 = (sum(diag(lamblamb.star))/
+              sum(diag(lamblamb.star + psi)))*100
> Gvcov = mat.loadings.star %*% t(mat.loadings.star) + psi
> 
> acc.m8 = NULL
> her.m8 = NULL
> for(i in 1:nlevels(data$Generation)){
+   pred_vcov = predict(M8, classify = "Genotype:Generation",

+   pred_sed = predict(M8, classify = "Genotype:Generation",
+                      level=list(Generation = i), sed = T)
+   pred_sed$pvals 
+   PEV = mean(diag(pred_vcov$vcov))
+   mvd = mean((pred_sed$sed^2)[upper.tri(pred_sed$sed^2,diag = F)])
+   acc.m8[i] = sqrt(1-(PEV/Gvcov[i,i]))
+   her.m8[i] = 1-(mvd/(2*Gvcov[i,i]))
